Day 20: Protected Routes Concept

A Protected Route is a route that can only be accessed by authenticated users.

Real-world Examples

✅ Logged-in users can access:

/dashboard
/profile
/orders
/settings

❌ Non-logged-in users cannot access them.

If they try, they are redirected to:

/login
Why Do We Need Protected Routes?

Suppose your app has:

/login
/dashboard
/profile

Without protection, anyone can type:

http://localhost:5173/dashboard

and access the page.

Protected Routes prevent this.

Concept
