More Reusable Version

Instead of:

<ProtectedRoute isAuthenticated={true}>
    <Dashboard />
</ProtectedRoute>

many applications use Context API or Redux to store login status.

Example:

const auth = useAuth();

Then:

if (!auth.isLoggedIn) {
    return <Navigate to="/login" />;
}

We'll learn this after Context API.

Example with Login Button
import { useNavigate } from "react-router-dom";

function Login() {

    const navigate = useNavigate();

    const handleLogin = () => {
        navigate("/dashboard");
    };

    return (
        <button onClick={handleLogin}>
            Login
        </button>
    );
}

export default Login;

